EzBot v0.0.1
WALL-E (441538296@qq.com)

OVERVIEW
========
EzBot is a simple irc bot for ezbox project (http://code.google.com/p/ezbox/).
It is derived from MartinchoBot (http://code.google.com/p/martinchobot/).

HOW TO USE IT
=============
This module requires Lua 5.1 (http://www.lua.org/), LuaSocket (http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~diego/professional/luasocket/)
and LuaExpat (http://www.keplerproject.org/luaexpat/).
First, edit config.lua, change bot name and server. Also, in config.lua is where new plugin definition should be placed.
Assuming that the lua interpreter is called "lua", then type: "lua ezbox.lua"
Then, from your irc client, send a message to EzBot, like: /msg EzBot !join #mychannel

And that's it!, the bot will join to #mychannel, ready to accept commands.

CHANGES
